  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to a simple dev-focused workflow so that I can manage and view the app's changelog.\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want up to date and accurate release notes so that I can follow progress.\r\n\r\nAs a marketer, I want an always up to date source of truth so that I can effectively broadcast to the community.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nStatus needs to provide a changelog/whats-new every release in Google Play and the App Store for users, as well as blog posts and emails. Currently this is done by a single person in #mobile-team in Google Docs but is a single point of failure, and doesn't involve the team's that actually create the features and update Status.  We can improve this by moving to a more decentralized way of creating a changelog.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\n[Keep a Changlelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/) proposes a standardised format for keeping changelog of your project repository in CHANGELOG.md file. This file contains a curated, chronologically ordered list of notable changes for each version of a project in human-readable format.\r\n\r\nThis is superior to our current silo'd changelog in google docs and is a single point of failure.  We can move from this to a changelog that everyone has visibility and ownership of.\r\n\r\nNext steps will be automating release notes in Testflight and Google Play using https://github.com/pajapro/fastlane-plugin-changelog\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3673765?s=400&v=4\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/favicon.ico\" height=\"14\"> GitHub</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/pajapro/fastlane-plugin-changelog\">pajapro/fastlane-plugin-changelog</a></strong></div><div>fastlane-plugin-changelog - Automate changes to your project CHANGELOG.md</div></blockquote>",
